   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Accelerated EFTofLSS predictions with `EFTEMU`\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook we introduce the `EFTEMU` that is part of the suite of emulators included with `matryoshka`. The purpose of this emulator is to accelerate EFTofLSS analyses. The emulator has been trained to predict the monopole $P_0$ and quandrupole $P_2$ returned by [PyBird](https://github.com/pierrexyz/pybird).\n",
    "\n",
    "We start by importing all the modules required for this example."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matryoshka.eft_funcs as MatEFT\n",
    "import matryoshka.halo_model_funcs as MatHM\n",
    "import matryoshka.emulator as MatEmu\n",
    "import matryoshka.plot as MatPlt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import time\n",
    "from scipy.optimize import minimize\n",
    "from scipy.stats import norm\n",
    "import zeus\n",
    "import corner"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next we load the cosmologies that for the train and test sets for `EFTEMU`. These training samples were chosen to overlap the [Aemulus](https://aemulusproject.github.io) and [AbacusSummit](https://abacussummit.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) simulation samples, and were generated using the `matryoshka.training_funcs.Resampler` class.\n",
    "\n",
    "It should be noted that these cosmological parameters are the **only** input for the NNs that the `EFTEMU` is based on.\n",
    "In equation 10 of [d'Amico et al. (2019)](https://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.1088/1475-7516/2020/05/005) they write the power spectrum as a sum of terms that are bias independant. Training the emulator to predict these bias independant terms rather than $P_0$ or $P_2$ directly is advantageous because it greatly reduces the dimensionality of the input."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],

   ]
  },

   "metadata": {},

   ]

    "Pct0_array = np.load(path_to_eft_data+\"Pct0_array-z0.51_noDQ1_optiresum-True.npy\")\n",
    "P112_array = np.load(path_to_eft_data+\"P112_array-z0.51_noDQ1_optiresum-True.npy\")\n",
    "Ploop2_array = np.load(path_to_eft_data+\"Ploop2_array-z0.51_noDQ1_optiresum-True.npy\")\n",
    "Pct2_array = np.load(path_to_eft_data+\"Pct2_array-z0.51_noDQ1_optiresum-True.npy\")\n",
    "\n",
    "test_id = np.load(\"/Users/jamie/Desktop/EFT/split/test.npy\")\n",
    "train_id = np.load(\"/Users/jamie/Desktop/EFT/split/train.npy\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We are not so interested in the prediction accuracy of these bias independant terms but rather the multipoles $P_0$ and $P_2$. This means that we need to generate multipoles from the bias free componenets, and this means we need to decide what bias parameters we should use.\n",
    "\n",
    "For this notebook we simply take random draws from the priors that were used in [d'Amico et al. (2019)](https://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.1088/1475-7516/2020/05/005) (equation 35). This will lead to some strange sets of bias parameters and may not be the best method to assess the predicion accuracy on $P_0$ and $P_2$, however it is the simplest.\n",
    "\n",
    "Define a simple function that will generate samples from the prior."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def random_bias(N):\n",
    "    b1 = np.random.uniform(0,4, size=N)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    c2 = np.random.uniform(-4,4, size=N)\n",
    "    c4 = np.random.normal(loc=0,scale=2, size=N)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    b2 = 1/np.sqrt(2)*(c2+c4)\n",
    "    b4 = 1/np.sqrt(2)*(c2-c4)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    b3 = np.random.normal(loc=0,scale=2, size=N)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    cct = np.random.normal(loc=0,scale=2, size=N)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    cr1 = np.random.normal(loc=0,scale=4, size=N)\n",
    "    cr2 = np.random.normal(loc=0,scale=2, size=N)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return np.vstack([b1, b2, b3, b4, cct, cr1, cr2]).T"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We generate random sets of bias parameters for each sample in the training and test sets."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1080x1080 with 49 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "random_bs = random_bias(cosmos.shape[0])\n",
    "\n",
    "bias_labels = [r\"$b_1$\", r\"$b_2$\", r\"$b_3$\", r\"$b_4$\", r\"$c_{ct}$\", r\"$c_{r1}$\", r\"$c_{r2}$\"]\n",
    "MatPlt.sample_space([random_bs], bias_labels)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can now calculate the multipoles."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "P0_train_test = np.zeros((cosmos.shape[0], MatEmu.kbird[:39].shape[0]))\n",
    "P2_train_test = np.zeros((cosmos.shape[0], MatEmu.kbird[:39].shape[0]))\n",
    "f_train_test = MatHM.fN_vec(cosmos[:,0]/cosmos[:,2]**2, 0.51)\n",
    "for i in range(cosmos.shape[0]):\n",
    "    f = MatHM.fN(cosmos[i,0]/cosmos[i,2]**2, 0.51)\n",
    "    P0_train_test[i,:] = MatEFT.multipole([P110_array[i],\n",
    "                                     Ploop0_array[i],\n",
    "                                     Pct0_array[i]],\n",
    "                                     random_bs[i],\n",
    "                                     f)[:39] # We impose a scale cut here as in the current version of matryoshka\n",
    "                                             # EFTEMU does not make predictions up to k=0.3h/Mpc\n",
    "    P2_train_test[i,:] = MatEFT.multipole([P112_array[i], \n",
    "                                     Ploop2_array[i],\n",
    "                                     Pct2_array[i]],\n",
    "                                     random_bs[i],\n",
    "                                     f)[:39]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},

   ]

    "P0_pred_std = np.quantile((P0_train_test[test_id]/P0_preds[test_id]-1),[0.16,1-0.16],axis=0)\n",
    "P0_pred_std = np.diff(P0_pred_std, axis=0)[0]/2\n",
    "P2_pred_std = np.quantile((P2_train_test[test_id]/P2_preds[test_id]-1),[0.16,1-0.16],axis=0)\n",
    "P2_pred_std = np.diff(P2_pred_std, axis=0)[0]/2\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(1)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(MatEmu.kbird[:39], P0_pred_std, label=r'$P_0$')\n",
    "plt.plot(MatEmu.kbird[:39], P2_pred_std, label=r'$P_2$')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel(r\"$k \\ [h \\ \\mathrm{Mpc}^{-1}]$\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(r\"$\\sigma(k) \\ [\\%]$\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To investigate how this level of prediction accuracy propgates into constraints on cosmological and bias parameters we run perform an MCMC using a $P_0$ and $P_2$ calculated using `PyBird` with the Planck 2018 $\\Lambda$CDM cosmology and reasonable bias parameters."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fid_bs = np.array([2., 1., 0.5, 0., 0.5, 2., 0.]) # These are the parameters from the PyBird example notebook.\n",
    "fid_cosmo = np.array([0.11933, 0.02242, 0.6766, 3.047, 0.9665])\n",
    "\n",
    "P110_P18 = np.load(path_to_eft_data+\"P110-z0.51_P18_optiresum-True.npy\")\n",
    "Ploop0_P18 = np.load(path_to_eft_data+\"Ploop0-z0.51_P18_optiresum-True.npy\")\n",
    "Pct0_P18 = np.load(path_to_eft_data+\"Pct0-z0.51_P18_optiresum-True.npy\")\n",
    "P112_P18 = np.load(path_to_eft_data+\"P112-z0.51_P18_optiresum-True.npy\")\n",
    "Ploop2_P18 = np.load(path_to_eft_data+\"Ploop2-z0.51_P18_optiresum-True.npy\")\n",
    "Pct2_P18 = np.load(path_to_eft_data+\"Pct2-z0.51_P18_optiresum-True.npy\")\n",
    "\n",
    "f = MatHM.fN(fid_cosmo[0]/fid_cosmo[2]**2, 0.51)\n",
    "P0_fid = MatEFT.multipole([P110_P18,\n",
    "                                 Ploop0_P18,Pct0_P18],fid_bs,f)[:39]\n",
    "P2_fid = MatEFT.multipole([P112_P18, \n",
    "                                 Ploop2_P18,Pct2_P18],fid_bs,f)[:39]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Before running our MCMC we can make predictions with the emulators and the true parameters."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x360 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "P0_fid_pred = P0_emu.emu_predict(fid_cosmo.reshape(1,-1), fid_bs.reshape(1,-1))[0]\n",
    "P2_fid_pred = P2_emu.emu_predict(fid_cosmo.reshape(1,-1), fid_bs.reshape(1,-1))[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(2,1, sharex=True, figsize=(8,5), gridspec_kw={'height_ratios': [3, 1]})\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[0].plot(MatEmu.kbird[:39], MatEmu.kbird[:39]*P0_fid, color=\"tab:blue\", label=\"PyBird\")\n",
    "ax[0].plot(MatEmu.kbird[:39], MatEmu.kbird[:39]*P0_fid_pred, color=\"blue\", linestyle='--', label=\"EFTEMU w/truth\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[0].plot(MatEmu.kbird[:39], MatEmu.kbird[:39]*P2_fid, color=\"tab:green\")\n",
    "ax[0].plot(MatEmu.kbird[:39], MatEmu.kbird[:39]*P2_fid_pred, color=\"green\", linestyle='--')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[1].plot(MatEmu.kbird[:39], P0_fid/P0_fid_pred, color=\"tab:blue\")\n",
    "ax[1].plot(MatEmu.kbird[:39], P2_fid/P2_fid_pred, color=\"tab:green\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[1].set_xlabel(r'$k \\ [h \\ \\mathrm{Mpc}^{-1}]$',fontsize='large')\n",
    "ax[0].set_ylabel(r'$kP_l(k) \\ [h^{-1} \\ \\mathrm{Mpc}]^2$',fontsize='large')\n",
    "ax[1].set_ylabel(r'$P_l^\\mathrm{emu.} \\ / \\ P_l^\\mathrm{EFT}$',fontsize='large')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[0].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We will be running our MCMC with [zeus](https://zeus-mcmc.readthedocs.io/en/latest/index.html). Bellow we define the functions that form the log probabolity that we will pass to `zeus`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Note that we will be using $c_2$ and $c_4$ rather than $b_2$ and $b_4$, this is following [d'Amico et al. (2019)](https://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.1088/1475-7516/2020/05/005) (see section 3.5)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def log_prior(x):\n",
    "    # Oc, Ob, h, As, ns\n",
    "    cosmo = x[:,:5]\n",
    "    # b1, c2, b3, c4, cct, cr1, cr2\n",
    "    bias = x[:,5:]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Flat prior on the cosmological parameters.\n",
    "    box_cosmo = np.greater(cosmo[:, 0], 0.10121926) & np.less(cosmo[:, 0], 0.13999676) \\\n",
    "        & np.greater(cosmo[:, 1], 0.02066472) & np.less(cosmo[:, 1], 0.02427991) \\\n",
    "        & np.greater(cosmo[:, 2], 0.57451438) & np.less(cosmo[:, 2], 0.74766042)\\\n",
    "        & np.greater(cosmo[:, 3], 2.77885117) & np.less(cosmo[:, 3], 3.32142323)\\\n",
    "        & np.greater(cosmo[:, 4], 0.90120542) & np.less(cosmo[:, 4], 1.02488991)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Flat prior on a selection of the bias parameters\n",
    "    box_bias = np.greater(bias[:, 0], 0.) & np.less(bias[:, 0], 4.) \\\n",
    "        & np.greater(bias[:, 1], -4.) & np.less(bias[:, 1], 4.)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return np.where(box_cosmo, 0, -np.inf)+np.where(box_bias, 0, -np.inf)\\\n",
    "           +norm.logpdf(bias[:,2], loc=0, scale=2)\\\n",
    "           +norm.logpdf(bias[:,3], loc=0, scale=2)\\\n",
    "           +norm.logpdf(bias[:,4], loc=0, scale=2)\\\n",
    "           +norm.logpdf(bias[:,5], loc=0, scale=4)\\\n",
    "           +norm.logpdf(bias[:,6], loc=0, scale=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "def log_like(x, obs, err):\n",
    "    # Oc, Ob, h, As, ns\n",
    "    cosmo = x[:,:5]\n",
    "    # b1, c2, b3, c4, cct, cr1, cr2\n",
    "    bias = x[:,5:]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    c2 = np.copy(bias[:,1])\n",
    "    c4 = np.copy(bias[:,3])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # b1, b2, b3, b4, cct, cr1, cr2\n",
    "    bias[:,1] = (c2+c4)/np.sqrt(2)\n",
    "    bias[:,3] = (c2-c4)/np.sqrt(2)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    P0_pred = P0_emu.emu_predict(cosmo, bias)\n",
    "    P2_pred = P2_emu.emu_predict(cosmo, bias)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    pred = np.hstack([P0_pred, P2_pred])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return -0.5*np.sum(((pred-obs)/(err*pred))**2, axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "def log_prob(theta, obs, err):\n",
    "    theta = np.vstack(theta)\n",
    "    lp = log_prior(theta)\n",
    "    ll = log_like(theta, obs, err)\n",
    "    return ll+lp\n",
    "\n",
    "def neg_log_prob(theta, obs, err):\n",
    "    theta = np.array(theta).reshape(1, -1)\n",
    "    return -(log_prob(theta, obs, err))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Before running our MCMC we quickly calculate the best fit parameters. With an inital guesses that are perturbations of the truth."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Optimization terminated successfully.\n",
      "         Current function value: 12.156676\n",
      "         Iterations: 750\n",
      "         Function evaluations: 1081\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "init_cosmo = np.copy(fid_cosmo)+1e-3*np.random.randn(5)\n",
    "init_bias = np.copy(fid_bs)+1e-2*np.random.randn(7)\n",
    "init_bias[1] = np.sqrt(2)/2*(fid_bs[1]+fid_bs[3])\n",
    "init_bias[3] = np.sqrt(2)/2*(fid_bs[1]-fid_bs[3])\n",
    "\n",
    "obs_pow = np.hstack([P0_fid, P2_fid])\n",
    "err = np.hstack([P0_pred_std, P2_pred_std])\n",
    "\n",
    "results = minimize(neg_log_prob, np.hstack([init_cosmo,init_bias]), args=(obs_pow, err),\n",
    "                   options={'disp': True, \"maxiter\": 100000}, method='Nelder-Mead')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can make predictions for the best fit parameters and plot these versus the truth."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x360 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "best_bias = results.x[5:]\n",
    "c2_best = best_bias[1]\n",
    "c4_best = best_bias[3]\n",
    "best_bias[1] = (c2_best+c4_best)/np.sqrt(2)\n",
    "best_bias[3] = (c2_best-c4_best)/np.sqrt(2)\n",
    "best_cosmo = results.x[:5]\n",
    "\n",
    "P0_best = P0_emu.emu_predict(best_cosmo.reshape(1,-1), best_bias.reshape(1,-1))[0]\n",
    "P2_best = P2_emu.emu_predict(best_cosmo.reshape(1,-1), best_bias.reshape(1,-1))[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(2,1, sharex=True, figsize=(8,5), gridspec_kw={'height_ratios': [3, 1]})\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[0].plot(MatEmu.kbird[:39], MatEmu.kbird[:39]*P0_fid, color=\"tab:blue\", label=\"PyBird\")\n",
    "ax[0].plot(MatEmu.kbird[:39], MatEmu.kbird[:39]*P0_best, color=\"blue\", linestyle='--', label=\"EFTEMU w/best\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[0].plot(MatEmu.kbird[:39], MatEmu.kbird[:39]*P2_fid, color=\"tab:green\")\n",
    "ax[0].plot(MatEmu.kbird[:39], MatEmu.kbird[:39]*P2_best, color=\"green\", linestyle='--')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[1].plot(MatEmu.kbird[:39], P0_fid/P0_best, color=\"tab:blue\")\n",
    "ax[1].plot(MatEmu.kbird[:39], P2_fid/P2_best, color=\"tab:green\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[1].set_xlabel(r'$k \\ [h \\ \\mathrm{Mpc}^{-1}]$',fontsize='large')\n",
    "ax[0].set_ylabel(r'$kP_l(k) \\ [h^{-1} \\ \\mathrm{Mpc}]^2$',fontsize='large')\n",
    "ax[1].set_ylabel(r'$P_l^\\mathrm{emu.} \\ / \\ P_l^\\mathrm{EFT}$',fontsize='large')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[0].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In the cell bellow we define the setup of our MCMC, as well as the inital positions of the walkers."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "nwalk = results.x.shape[0]*2\n",
    "ndim = results.x.shape[0]\n",
    "init_pos = results.x+1e-4*np.random.randn(nwalk, ndim)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We will be moinitoring convergence of our chains by monitoring the autocorrelation time, once we have run for more than $50\\tau$ and our estimate of $\\tau$ has converged to within $1\\%$ we will stop the chain. `zeus` has in-built functions that allow us to do this very easily."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cb0 = zeus.callbacks.AutocorrelationCallback(ncheck=100, dact=0.01, nact=50, discard=0.5)\n",
    "cb1 = zeus.callbacks.MinIterCallback(nmin=1000)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we finally run our MCMC!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Initialising ensemble of 24 walkers...\n",
      "Sampling progress :  27%|██████████████▎                                      | 2700/10000 [04:19<11:41, 10.41it/s]"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "335447 likelihood evaluations in 4.3 minutes.\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sampler = zeus.EnsembleSampler(nwalk, ndim, log_prob, args=(obs_pow,err), vectorize=True)\n",
    "start = time.time()\n",
    "sampler.run_mcmc(init_pos, 10000, progress=True, callbacks=[cb0, cb1])\n",
    "end = time.time()\n",
    "print(\"{a} likelihood evaluations in {b} minutes.\".format(a=sampler.ncall, b=np.round((end-start)/60,1)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We discard the first $5\\tilde{\\tau}$ steps in the chain and produce trace plots for each of the variables."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x1080 with 24 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "discard = zeus.AutoCorrTime(sampler.get_chain()).mean()*5\n",
    "chain = sampler.get_chain(flat=False, discard=int(discard))\n",
    "flat_chain = sampler.get_chain(flat=True, discard=int(discard))\n",
    "\n",
    "param_labels = [r\"$\\omega_c$\",r\"$\\omega_b$\",r\"$h$\",r\"$A_s$\",r\"$n_s$\", r\"$b_1$\", r\"$c_2$\",\n",
    "                r\"$b_3$\", r\"$c_4$\", r\"$c_{ct}$\", r\"$c_{r1}$\", r\"$c_{r2}$\"]\n",
    "truths = np.hstack([fid_cosmo, np.array(fid_bs)])\n",
    "truths[5+1] = np.sqrt(2)/2*(fid_bs[1]+fid_bs[3])\n",
    "truths[5+3] = np.sqrt(2)/2*(fid_bs[1]-fid_bs[3])\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(12,2, figsize=(10,15), gridspec_kw={'width_ratios':[3,1]}, sharex='col', sharey='row')\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(12):\n",
    "    ax[i,0].plot(chain[:,:,i])\n",
    "    ax[i,0].set_ylabel(param_labels[i])\n",
    "    ax[i,1].hist(chain[:,:,i].flatten(),bins=50, orientation='horizontal')\n",
    "    #ax[i,1].set_frame_on(False)\n",
    "    ax[i,1].set_xticks([])\n",
    "    for j in range(2):\n",
    "        ax[i,j].axhline(truths[i], color='red')\n",
    "        for q in [0.025, 0.975]:\n",
    "            ax[i,j].axhline(np.quantile(chain[:,:,i].flatten(), q), color='k', linestyle='--')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[-1,0].set_xlabel(\"Steps after burn-in\")\n",
    "plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.1, wspace=0.)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We then produce a corner plot using the [corner](https://corner.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) package. Before plotting we apply some rescaling such that the means of each of the marginalised 1D posteriors is $\\mathcal{O}(1)$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [

      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "param_labels = [r\"$10\\omega_c$\",r\"$100\\omega_b$\",r\"$10h$\",r\"$A_s$\",r\"$10n_s$\", r\"$b_1$\", r\"$10c_2$\",\n",
    "                r\"$10b_3$\", r\"$10c_4$\", r\"$10c_{ct}$\", r\"$c_{r1}$\", r\"$10c_{r2}$\"]\n",
    "flat_chain[:,[0,1,2,4,6,7,8,9,11]] = flat_chain[:,[0,1,2,4,6,7,8,9,11]]*10\n",
    "truths[[0,1,2,4,6,7,8,9,11]] = truths[[0,1,2,4,6,7,8,9,11]]*10\n",
    "flat_chain[:,1] = flat_chain[:,1]*10\n",
    "truths[1] = truths[1]*10\n",
    "corner.corner(flat_chain, labels=param_labels, truths=truths, show_titles=True);"
   ]
